  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Promoting Inclusive Action in Peacebuilding (PIAP Initiative)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The overarching goal of the project is to reduce inter-communal conflict over natural resources in Marka District, Somalia by supporting young people who are primarily, though not exclusively, from the Biyomal and Habargidir sub-clans to lead the development of inclusive and participatory resource management mechanisms and governance systems. Young people from displaced communities, minority clans, and young people with disabilities are also incorporated into the project activities.</narrative>
  </description>
